laboratory_examinations.findings: Subsegmental atelectasis at the lung bases. The visualized heart and great vessels are within normal limits. In the left lobe of the liver, there are two hypoattenuating lesions, one measuring 14 mm and a second measuring 17 mm. Additionally, there is a 1.7 x 2.7 x 1.5 cm hypoattenuating lesion in the posterior right lobe of the liver. The hepatic veins and portal venous system are grossly patent. No intra- or extra-hepatic biliary duct dilatation identified. The gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys are within normal limits. The fluid-filled appendix measures 10 mm, with significant periappendiceal fat stranding, consistent with acute appendicitis. No extraluminal air or adjacent fluid collection to suggest perforation.
